make up the parallel CG-FFT DDA program. The different makefiles
1) Makefile
2) make_mpi_s
3) make_mpi_d
4) make_pvm_s
5) make_seq_s
6) make_seq_d
and their functions are described in Makefile. The input-files
1) Romb4.dat
2) Romb5.dat
3) Romb6.dat
4) Romb7.dat
5) Romb8.dat
specify the accuracy to which the Romberg-routine should integrate. 
Min and max are the lower and upper boundary of the integration-interval
respectively, JMAX is the number of times the integration interval must 
be refined, K is the number of values to be used in the extrapolation,
and epsilon finally is the convergence criterium. For a detailed 
for a detailed description of this integration-procedure see 
"Application of the discrete dipole approximation to radiation pressure
calculatinos on dust-aggregates: An exploration".
